article.description: — Moussa Cisse scored 14 points with nine rebounds and Memphis beat East Carolina 80-53 on Sunday.
article.headline: Cisse scores 14 to carry Memphis past East Carolina 80-53
article.linkText: Cisse scores 14 to carry Memphis past East Carolina 80-53
article.story: GREENVILLE, N.C. -- — Moussa Cisse scored 14 points with nine rebounds and Memphis beat East Carolina 80-53 on Sunday. DeAndre Williams had 11 points and seven rebounds for Memphis (8-5, 4-2 American Athletic Conference). Boogie Ellis scored 11 points and Landers Nolley II had seven rebounds. Memphis dominated the first half and led 49-18 at halftime. The Pirates’ 18 first-half points were a season low for the team. Tremont Robinson-White had 15 points for the Pirates (7-4, 1-4), Brandon Suggs scored 11 and Tristen Newton 10. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
